Victor first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]], one of ten CDPS ([[Acampo, California|Acampo]], [[Collierville, California|Collierville]], [[Dogtown, San Joaquin County, California|Dogtown]], [[Mountain House, California|Mountain House]], [[Peters, California|Peters]], [[Terminous, California|Terminous]], [[Thornton, California|Thornton]], Victor, [[Waterloo, California|Waterloo]], and [[Woodbridge, California|Woodbridge]]) formed out of the deleted [[North Woodbridge, California|North Woodbridge CDP]] and [[South Woodbridge, California|South Woodbridge CDP]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Victor had a population of 313. The population density was {{convert|247.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup was 148 (47.3%) [[White Americans|White]], 0 (0.0%) [[African Americans|African American]], 5 (1.6%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 8 (2.6%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 3 (1.0%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 79 (25.2%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 70 (22.4%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 185 persons (59.1%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Victor CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0682562 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=July 12, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 118 households, out of which 35 (29.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 71 (60.2%) were married-couple households, 3 (2.5%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 23 (19.5%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 21 (17.8%) had a male householder with no partner present. 28 households (23.7%) were one person, and 9 (7.6%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.65.<ref name=DP1/> There were 87 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (73.7% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Victor CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0682562 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=July 12, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 93 people (29.7%) under the age of 18, 26 people (8.3%) aged 18 to 24, 69 people (22.0%) aged 25 to 44, 84 people (26.8%) aged 45 to 64, and 41 people (13.1%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 39.2{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 101.9 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 123 housing units at an average density of {{convert|97.4|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 118 (95.9%) were occupied. Of these, 113 (95.8%) were owner-occupied, and 5 (4.2%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

